911 434 M 
-0.200 0 (  \(nico@bredex.de\))A 
; : 161 659 550 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 659 M 
-0.200 0 (Swapping of containers)A 
; : 161 704 550 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 704 M 
-0.200 0 (======================)A 
; : 161 794 1125 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 794 M 
-0.200 0 (The standard library lacks some specification)A 
; : 161 839 1000 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 839 M 
-0.200 0 (about how a swap\(\) works for containers.)A 
; : 161 974 400 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 974 M 
-0.200 0 (Actual situation)A 
; : 161 1019 400 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1019 M 
-0.200 0 (----------------)A 
; : 161 1109 1400 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1109 M 
-0.200 0 (The definitions in the draft actually say the following:)A 
; : 161 1154 1050 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1154 M 
-0.200 0 ( - Any container member function a.swap\(b\))A 
; : 161 1199 1175 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1199 M 
-0.200 0 (   has the post-condition swap\(a,b\) \(see 23.1\).)A 
; : 161 1244 750 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1244 M 
-0.200 0 ( - The global algorithm swap\(\))A 
; : 161 1289 1375 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1289 M 
-0.200 0 (   "exchanges values stored in two locations" \(25.2.2\).)A 
; : 161 1334 1125 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1334 M 
-0.200 0 ( - For every container it is specified that a)A 
; : 161 1379 1225 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1379 M 
-0.200 0 (   specialized global algorithms swap\(x,y\) exist,)A 
; : 161 1424 1175 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1424 M 
-0.200 0 (   which effects s.swap\(y\) \(see e.g. 23.2.4.4\).)A 
; : 161 1469 1125 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1469 M 
-0.200 0 ( - For containers swap\(\) should have constant)A 
; : 161 1514 525 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1514 M 
-0.200 0 (   complexity \(23.1\).)A 
; : 161 1559 1250 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1559 M 
-0.200 0 ( - Regarding exceptions 23.1 states the following:)A 
; : 161 1604 1450 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1604 M 
-0.200 0 (     > All container types defined in this clause meet the)A 
; : 161 1649 1525 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1649 M 
-0.200 0 (     > additional requirements that no swap\(\) function throws)A 
; : 161 1694 1450 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1694 M 
-0.200 0 (     > an exception unless that exception is thrown by the)A 
; : 161 1739 1325 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1739 M 
-0.200 0 (     > copy constructor or assignment operator of the)A 
; : 161 1784 1375 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1784 M 
-0.200 0 (     > container's Compare object \(if any, see 23.1.2\).)A 
; : 161 1829 1125 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1829 M 
-0.200 0 ( - For basic_string the following is defined:)A 
; : 161 1874 1375 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1874 M 
-0.200 0 (     > References, pointers, and iterators referring to)A 
; : 161 1919 1625 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1919 M 
-0.200 0 (     > the elements of a basic_string sequence may be invalidated)A 
; : 161 1964 1425 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 1964 M 
-0.200 0 (     > by the following uses of that basic_string object:)A 
; : 161 2009 1725 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2009 M 
-0.200 0 (     >  - As an argument to non-member functions swap\(\) \(21.3.7.8\)...)A 
; : 161 2054 1225 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2054 M 
-0.200 0 (     >  - As an argument to basic_string::swap\(\).)A 
; : 161 2189 175 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2189 M 
-0.200 0 (Defects)A 
; : 161 2234 175 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2234 M 
-0.200 0 (-------)A 
; : 161 2324 1025 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2324 M 
-0.200 0 (The current specifications of swap\(\) have)A 
; : 161 2369 575 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2369 M 
-0.200 0 (the following problems:)A 
; : 161 2414 1275 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2414 M 
-0.200 0 ( - There is no general statement about what happens)A 
; : 161 2459 1100 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2459 M 
-0.200 0 (   with references, pointers, and iterators.)A 
; : 161 2504 1200 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2504 M 
-0.200 0 (   Following the idea of the specialized swap\(\)s)A 
; : 161 2549 1175 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2549 M 
-0.200 0 (   it seems to make sense that they are swapped)A 
; : 161 2594 875 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2594 M 
-0.200 0 (   accordingly and thus stay valid.)A 
; : 161 2639 1175 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2639 M 
-0.200 0 (   As \(except for string\) there is no statement)A 
; : 161 2684 1150 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2684 M 
-0.200 0 (   about that, it implicitly means that swap\(\))A 
; : 161 2729 1525 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2729 M 
-0.200 0 (   currently invalidates references, pointers, and iterators.)A 
; : 161 2774 1375 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2774 M 
-0.200 0 (   Changing that would enable significant advantages as)A 
; : 161 2819 1175 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2819 M 
-0.200 0 (   people could swap containers without loosing)A 
; : 161 2864 925 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2864 M 
-0.200 0 (   references to individual elements.)A 
; : 161 2909 1250 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2909 M 
-0.200 0 ( - Another related aspect is the question, whether)A 
; : 161 2954 1075 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2954 M 
-0.200 0 (   a vector might reallocate due to swap\(\).)A 
; : 161 2999 1400 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2999 M 
-0.200 0 (   Actually there is no statement about that, what means)A 
; : 161 3044 825 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 3044 M 
-0.200 0 (   that reallocation might occur.)A 
; 
